1
00:00:12,360 --> 00:00:16,190
[Hanzhou City; 2002]

2
00:00:16,190 --> 00:00:17,120
Sleeping again?

3
00:00:17,960 --> 00:00:18,920
You scared me.

4
00:00:19,710 --> 00:00:20,440
How did it go?

5
00:00:22,230 --> 00:00:23,290
Couldn't find her.

6
00:00:23,550 --> 00:00:24,810
The teacher resigned.

7
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:28,000
Her colleague said she immigrated.

8
00:00:28,870 --> 00:00:29,730
So she ran away.

9
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:31,600
Senior Hongchao.

10
00:00:32,350 --> 00:00:34,030
How do we continue
investigating this case?

11
00:00:34,030 --> 00:00:35,240
There's no case we can't solve.

12
00:00:35,240 --> 00:00:37,440
Just investigate as we normally would.

13
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:39,670
Call Xu Li.

14
00:00:39,670 --> 00:00:40,840
Ask her whether

15
00:00:41,320 --> 00:00:43,150
any of her classmates
or other teachers

16
00:00:43,150 --> 00:00:44,280
knew about this.

17
00:00:44,280 --> 00:00:46,280
Yes, I'm looking for
the phone number right now.

18
00:00:46,280 --> 00:00:47,180
Here's the number.

19
00:00:47,180 --> 00:00:48,430
I found it.

20
00:00:59,390 --> 00:00:59,920
Xu Li.

21
00:01:00,430 --> 00:01:01,790
This is Mai Hongchao.

22
00:01:01,790 --> 00:01:02,850
Do you remember me?

23
00:01:03,920 --> 00:01:04,650
Officer Mai.

24
00:01:05,069 --> 00:01:07,280
Could you please stop investigating?

25
00:01:08,560 --> 00:01:09,200
Why?

26
00:01:10,840 --> 00:01:12,200
My classmates are saying I'm lying.

27
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:14,450
I really don't want the police
involved anymore.

28
00:01:14,450 --> 00:01:15,610
Officer Mai.

29
00:01:15,680 --> 00:01:18,000
I'm begging you to stop the investigation.

30
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:20,200
I don't want them
coming to my house again.

31
00:01:20,200 --> 00:01:21,789
I'm really scared.

32
00:01:23,820 --> 00:01:25,530
Someone came to your house?

33
00:01:26,060 --> 00:01:26,710
Listen.

34
00:01:26,710 --> 00:01:28,590
Lock your doors right now, okay?

35
00:01:28,590 --> 00:01:30,450
Don't worry. We'll be there soon.

36
00:01:30,950 --> 00:01:31,810
Something's happened at Xu Li's place.

37
00:01:31,810 --> 00:01:33,009
-Let’s go.
-Let’s go.

38
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:56,070
What happened?

39
00:01:56,640 --> 00:01:57,350
Who are you?

40
00:01:57,729 --> 00:01:58,789
We're from the Criminal Investigation Unit
of the Municipal Bureau.

41
00:01:58,789 --> 00:01:59,430
What's going on here?

42
00:01:59,430 --> 00:02:00,120
[Guazi, the Assassin]

43
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:01,720
A young girl slit her wrists.

44
00:02:01,790 --> 00:02:03,200
Before the ambulance arrived,

45
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:04,400
she was already dead.

46
00:02:04,550 --> 00:02:06,010
What's the victim's name?

47
00:02:06,040 --> 00:02:06,840
Her name is...

48
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:07,760
Xu Li.

49
00:02:08,110 --> 00:02:08,800
Xu Li?

50
00:02:10,470 --> 00:02:11,600
She slit her wrists?

51
00:02:11,940 --> 00:02:14,590
[Leng Shan, Xu Li's friend]

52
00:03:32,030 --> 00:03:42,210
[The Punishment]

53
00:03:42,430 --> 00:03:42,740
[Punish those who commit crimes
and make mistakes]

54
00:03:42,740 --> 00:03:43,060
[so as to discipline them,]

55
00:03:43,060 --> 00:03:43,690
[and execute those
who violate the prohibitions]

56
00:03:43,690 --> 00:03:44,960
[so as to terrify would-be violators.]

57
00:03:44,980 --> 00:03:46,180
[Guanzi – On Laws and Standards]

58
00:03:46,860 --> 00:03:49,829
[Episode 4]

59
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:50,390
Director Peng.

60
00:03:50,390 --> 00:03:50,710
[Outstanding Worker]

61
00:03:50,710 --> 00:03:51,960
How's the tea?

62
00:03:52,430 --> 00:03:53,470
If you like it,

63
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:55,640
I can get you another can.

64
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:57,400
Qin Feng used to

65
00:03:57,590 --> 00:03:58,870
perform really well

66
00:03:58,870 --> 00:04:00,350
when he was at the bureau.

67
00:04:01,030 --> 00:04:02,030
But, Zhong,

68
00:04:02,960 --> 00:04:04,620
I need you to keep an eye on him.

69
00:04:05,240 --> 00:04:08,100
His relationship
with Hu Xiaoyue is quite special.

70
00:04:08,110 --> 00:04:08,960
I'm worried

71
00:04:10,150 --> 00:04:11,680
he might mess things up.

72
00:04:12,060 --> 00:04:12,120
[Hanzhou Public Security Bureau]

73
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:13,030
I think

74
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:15,860
ability is one thing,
character is another.

75
00:04:16,160 --> 00:04:18,240
He can't just be skilled
without good character.

76
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:20,240
Look at the scene he caused that day.

77
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:21,839
Wasn't he making fools of us?

78
00:04:22,390 --> 00:04:24,920
Let's not bring up
what's already in the past.

79
00:04:26,120 --> 00:04:27,720
I wonder what Director Ye

80
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:29,830
is really thinking.

81
00:04:29,830 --> 00:04:31,090
It's nothing special.

82
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:35,040
A leader transferring
someone he knows to work by his side—

83
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:36,159
that's perfectly normal.

84
00:04:36,159 --> 00:04:37,310
But he can't just say the word

85
00:04:37,310 --> 00:04:38,840
and transfer someone over.

86
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:40,190
I don't mind,

87
00:04:40,830 --> 00:04:43,960
but he should at least
consult with you and Director Yan.

88
00:04:48,920 --> 00:04:49,950
The two of us

89
00:04:50,360 --> 00:04:51,490
have no objections.

90
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:57,590
Shouldn't we build a better relationship
with Director Ye?

91
00:04:57,590 --> 00:04:59,480
You've just been transferred
back to the bureau, right?

92
00:04:59,480 --> 00:05:00,390
Investigation is one thing,

93
00:05:00,390 --> 00:05:02,520
but don't let others trip you up again.

94
00:05:03,070 --> 00:05:05,020
You idiot—now you're lecturing me?

95
00:05:05,020 --> 00:05:06,140
How am I an idiot?

96
00:05:07,870 --> 00:05:09,000
I just got back.

97
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:10,560
At this stage,

98
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:12,700
no matter who I'm close to,

99
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:14,920
I shouldn't be close to Director Ye.

100
00:05:15,000 --> 00:05:15,760
Why?

101
00:05:16,480 --> 00:05:19,660
Director Yan and Director Peng
were both about to be promoted,

102
00:05:19,660 --> 00:05:21,420
but then Director Ye was transferred here,

103
00:05:21,420 --> 00:05:23,240
and everyone had to stay put.

104
00:05:23,270 --> 00:05:25,160
How could they
not have feelings about that?

105
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:27,290
I was transferred here by Director Ye.

106
00:05:27,380 --> 00:05:29,640
If I'm constantly seen with Director Ye,

107
00:05:29,710 --> 00:05:31,970
how could others not have issues with me?

108
00:05:32,230 --> 00:05:33,750
[Hanzhou Public Security Bureau]

109
00:05:33,750 --> 00:05:34,750
Tell me the truth.

110
00:05:36,120 --> 00:05:37,510
Do you have something on your mind?

111
00:05:37,510 --> 00:05:38,360
No.

112
00:05:38,360 --> 00:05:40,020
I don't have anything in mind.

113
00:05:41,510 --> 00:05:43,590
I'm just a bit worried.

114
00:05:44,340 --> 00:05:46,270
Qin Feng has joined my department.

115
00:05:46,510 --> 00:05:48,390
With his connection to Director Ye,

116
00:05:48,390 --> 00:05:50,300
I don't know how to manage him.

117
00:05:50,390 --> 00:05:52,430
Just manage him as you should.

118
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:55,510
If there's no discipline,

119
00:05:55,510 --> 00:05:57,170
won't everything fall apart?

120
00:05:57,240 --> 00:05:57,920
Yes.

121
00:06:00,970 --> 00:06:03,430
I haven't been
at the Municipal Bureau long,

122
00:06:04,920 --> 00:06:06,650
never worked with Director Ye,

123
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:10,120
and don't know
what kind of temperament he has.

124
00:06:10,310 --> 00:06:11,830
What does Director Ye's temperament

125
00:06:11,830 --> 00:06:13,960
have to do with how you manage Qin Feng?

126
00:06:14,310 --> 00:06:15,830
Absolutely nothing.

127
00:06:17,390 --> 00:06:18,610
You're overthinking things all day.

128
00:06:18,610 --> 00:06:22,750
[Hanzhou Public Security Bureau]

129
00:06:22,750 --> 00:06:24,350
Careful, I just refilled it.

130
00:06:26,080 --> 00:06:27,110
You know what,

131
00:06:27,480 --> 00:06:29,280
your tea is actually quite good.

132
00:06:30,830 --> 00:06:31,930
Actually,

133
00:06:32,680 --> 00:06:33,930
At work,

134
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:35,000
Ye can be tough

135
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:36,200
and uncompromising,

136
00:06:36,830 --> 00:06:39,159
but in person
he's actually quite easygoing.

137
00:06:39,159 --> 00:06:40,310
Don't overthink things.

138
00:06:40,310 --> 00:06:42,480
Just focus on doing your job well.

139
00:06:42,950 --> 00:06:44,150
When you do good work,

140
00:06:44,360 --> 00:06:45,960
the leadership will notice.

141
00:06:46,159 --> 00:06:46,830
Yes.

142
00:06:47,360 --> 00:06:49,159
That's exactly what I think too.

143
00:06:51,070 --> 00:06:52,250
I understand

144
00:06:52,510 --> 00:06:53,560
how you feel.

145
00:06:53,750 --> 00:06:54,560
After all,

146
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:56,570
you're getting to that age.

147
00:06:57,040 --> 00:06:57,870
Don't worry.

148
00:06:58,360 --> 00:06:59,290
I'm not worried.

149
00:06:59,360 --> 00:06:59,960
Not at all.

150
00:07:01,510 --> 00:07:03,040
What are you talking about?

151
00:07:03,430 --> 00:07:04,890
-Captain Ji, come on.
-Ji.

152
00:07:04,920 --> 00:07:05,600
Come on.

153
00:07:05,950 --> 00:07:08,030
I prefer being called Ji.

154
00:07:08,050 --> 00:07:09,910
What's this Captain Ji nonsense?

155
00:07:10,270 --> 00:07:11,120
Come on. Sit down.

156
00:07:11,120 --> 00:07:13,120
Look how healthy our old chief eats.

157
00:07:14,270 --> 00:07:16,270
You young guys should eat more meat.

158
00:07:16,950 --> 00:07:18,830
It's not often
the three of us get together again.

159
00:07:18,830 --> 00:07:19,680
That's right.

160
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:21,410
-It's rare.
-It's rare indeed.

161
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:24,040
The three musketeers
of Gutang Town are reunited.

162
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:25,240
But, Crazy,

163
00:07:25,630 --> 00:07:27,560
don't think I'm nagging you again.

164
00:07:27,950 --> 00:07:29,310
Now that you're at the Municipal Bureau,

165
00:07:29,310 --> 00:07:32,110
you need to be more careful
about how you do things.

166
00:07:34,490 --> 00:07:35,740
I know why

167
00:07:35,920 --> 00:07:37,470
you were transferred back here.

168
00:07:37,470 --> 00:07:39,040
But I want to give you some advice:

169
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:40,600
tone down that crazy attitude of yours.

170
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:42,159
Do you realize how many eyes

171
00:07:42,159 --> 00:07:44,560
are watching you in your current position?

172
00:07:44,650 --> 00:07:45,390
Also,

173
00:07:46,190 --> 00:07:47,680
many people had objections

174
00:07:47,680 --> 00:07:49,600
to your transfer this time.

175
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:51,390
Bro,

176
00:07:51,390 --> 00:07:52,990
are you really lecturing me?

177
00:07:54,159 --> 00:07:54,870
If we're

178
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:56,159
talking about

179
00:07:56,590 --> 00:07:57,590
this place,

180
00:07:58,950 --> 00:08:00,580
then I'm your senior.

181
00:08:00,960 --> 00:08:03,310
Where were you when I was working here?

182
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:05,000
I was transferred out from here.

183
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:06,400
Now you're lecturing me?

184
00:08:06,430 --> 00:08:07,310
That's true.

185
00:08:07,330 --> 00:08:08,070
Look at him,

186
00:08:08,110 --> 00:08:09,000
so smug.

187
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:10,080
Senior,

188
00:08:10,890 --> 00:08:11,880
weren't you

189
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:13,070
demoted to my department

190
00:08:13,070 --> 00:08:14,530
because you made mistakes?

191
00:08:14,530 --> 00:08:16,790
-You made mistakes.
-Yes, I got demoted.

192
00:08:17,830 --> 00:08:18,750
So,

193
00:08:19,510 --> 00:08:20,750
control your temper.

194
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:22,070
Don't make any more mistakes,

195
00:08:22,070 --> 00:08:24,000
or you might get demoted again.

196
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:25,060
That won't happen.

197
00:08:25,070 --> 00:08:25,600
Tao,

198
00:08:25,830 --> 00:08:26,630
keep an eye on him.

199
00:08:26,630 --> 00:08:28,630
Don't worry. I can keep him in check.

200
00:08:45,720 --> 00:08:48,050
Captain Zhong, take it easy.
Don't hurt yourself.

201
00:08:48,050 --> 00:08:48,910
Captain Zhong.

202
00:08:51,550 --> 00:08:52,480
Thank you.

203
00:08:52,480 --> 00:08:53,910
You're in great shape.

204
00:08:54,480 --> 00:08:55,620
Here, Captain Zhong.

205
00:08:55,620 --> 00:08:56,260
Okay.

206
00:09:02,140 --> 00:09:03,140
Thank you.

207
00:09:04,480 --> 00:09:05,660
How does it feel

208
00:09:06,040 --> 00:09:07,300
on your first day back?

209
00:09:08,170 --> 00:09:10,370
The atmosphere at the Municipal Bureau

210
00:09:10,430 --> 00:09:11,360
is really great.

211
00:09:11,930 --> 00:09:13,360
We were just talking about it.

212
00:09:13,360 --> 00:09:14,550
I said, with such a good atmosphere,

213
00:09:14,550 --> 00:09:16,940
you can tell at a glance it's a team
led by Captain Zhong.

214
00:09:16,940 --> 00:09:19,400
Enough. Enough.

215
00:09:20,280 --> 00:09:22,170
S-Stop flattering me.

216
00:09:25,510 --> 00:09:26,500
Qin.

217
00:09:27,420 --> 00:09:29,230
Since you're back now,

218
00:09:30,130 --> 00:09:32,270
let me be frank with you.

219
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:35,720
From now on,

220
00:09:35,780 --> 00:09:38,980
you need to forget
those police station methods.

221
00:09:39,450 --> 00:09:40,090
Yes.

222
00:09:40,950 --> 00:09:43,750
I want to make my position
clear to you, Captain Zhong.

223
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:44,870
Although

224
00:09:45,150 --> 00:09:47,180
Director Ye transferred me here,

225
00:09:47,210 --> 00:09:49,390
since I'm in your department now

226
00:09:49,480 --> 00:09:50,670
and under your command,

227
00:09:50,670 --> 00:09:52,000
I'm your soldier.

228
00:09:52,440 --> 00:09:54,260
I'll go wherever you point me.

229
00:09:54,410 --> 00:09:55,750
I'll follow all your orders.

230
00:09:55,750 --> 00:09:56,840
Good.

231
00:09:57,250 --> 00:09:58,990
With that commitment,

232
00:09:59,120 --> 00:10:01,670
I'll be completely
straightforward with you.

233
00:10:01,670 --> 00:10:02,390
Come on.

234
00:10:02,570 --> 00:10:06,030
-Sit down. Let's sit down and talk.
-Thank you, Captain Zhong.

235
00:10:09,750 --> 00:10:10,550
Qin.

236
00:10:12,150 --> 00:10:13,240
What do you think

237
00:10:14,030 --> 00:10:16,120
about the case
Captain Hu discussed

238
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,270
with you earlier?

239
00:10:21,540 --> 00:10:22,400
Captain Zhong,

240
00:10:22,800 --> 00:10:24,640
honestly, I haven't figured out

241
00:10:25,850 --> 00:10:27,380
how to handle this case yet.

242
00:10:27,910 --> 00:10:29,840
Just tell me what you're thinking.

243
00:10:32,270 --> 00:10:35,040
Actually, this case mainly depends on

244
00:10:35,080 --> 00:10:36,440
the missing Wang Ming.

245
00:10:37,470 --> 00:10:39,140
But I checked before

246
00:10:39,390 --> 00:10:41,820
and he was taken away
by two police officers.

247
00:10:41,820 --> 00:10:43,690
But there's something
complicated

248
00:10:43,690 --> 00:10:44,650
about this.

249
00:10:45,050 --> 00:10:45,980
Tell me about it.

250
00:10:47,410 --> 00:10:48,270
Captain Zhong.

251
00:10:48,370 --> 00:10:49,230
How about this?

252
00:10:49,260 --> 00:10:51,400
This case is indeed quite significant.

253
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:53,260
I'll go back and investigate further.

254
00:10:53,260 --> 00:10:55,660
I'll report to you
as soon as I have results.

255
00:10:56,040 --> 00:10:57,170
Quite significant?

256
00:10:58,230 --> 00:10:59,390
How significant is it?

257
00:10:59,390 --> 00:11:00,600
This case, well...

258
00:11:02,450 --> 00:11:03,650
Keep your voice down.

259
00:11:05,940 --> 00:11:06,660
Well,

260
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:08,260
these two people...

261
00:11:08,390 --> 00:11:09,290
They're fake police officers.

262
00:11:09,290 --> 00:11:09,910
Yes.

263
00:11:11,550 --> 00:11:13,350
What's so secretive about that?

264
00:11:13,360 --> 00:11:15,090
This is a very serious offense.

265
00:11:15,390 --> 00:11:17,050
How much evidence do you have?

266
00:11:17,180 --> 00:11:19,310
We have some. Show it to Captain Zhong.

267
00:11:19,760 --> 00:11:20,960
Here, Captain Zhong.

268
00:11:28,890 --> 00:11:30,220
Captain Zhong, you see—

269
00:11:30,350 --> 00:11:32,150
even the badge numbers are fake.

270
00:11:32,160 --> 00:11:34,440
This matter must be
thoroughly investigated.

271
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:35,440
-Yes.
-You need to take this seriously.

272
00:11:35,440 --> 00:11:37,300
Right, I'm investigating it now.

273
00:11:37,910 --> 00:11:38,580
Well then.

274
00:11:39,570 --> 00:11:41,430
I'll think about this carefully.

275
00:11:41,490 --> 00:11:42,840
If you can

276
00:11:43,630 --> 00:11:44,870
dig up more

277
00:11:44,870 --> 00:11:46,390
valuable clues,

278
00:11:47,060 --> 00:11:48,780
it'll be easier for me
to talk to the leadership.

279
00:11:48,780 --> 00:11:50,840
-Thank you, Captain Zhong.
-You have to get to the bottom of it.

280
00:11:50,840 --> 00:11:51,800
Yes, we will.

281
00:11:52,010 --> 00:11:53,440
Okay. Alright.

282
00:11:54,030 --> 00:11:55,270
I'll get back to work now.

283
00:11:55,270 --> 00:11:57,070
Please go ahead, Captain Zhong.

284
00:11:57,500 --> 00:11:58,220
Okay.

285
00:12:02,810 --> 00:12:04,720
I never noticed
when we were at the station

286
00:12:04,720 --> 00:12:06,150
that you, with your honest face,

287
00:12:06,150 --> 00:12:07,480
were so good
at providing emotional support.

288
00:12:07,480 --> 00:12:08,860
Are you managing up?

289
00:12:08,880 --> 00:12:10,550
Managing up

290
00:12:10,750 --> 00:12:12,390
is about the "up."

291
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:16,140
When I was at the station,
where was there any room to manage up?

292
00:12:16,140 --> 00:12:17,930
Then later, give me
some emotional support

293
00:12:17,930 --> 00:12:18,730
and manage me.

294
00:12:18,990 --> 00:12:19,990
You don't need it.

295
00:12:19,990 --> 00:12:21,250
Why wouldn't I need it?

296
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:23,480
What if I become a captain one day?

297
00:12:23,480 --> 00:12:24,200
Right?

298
00:12:27,220 --> 00:12:29,820
The way you exercise now
is very captain-like.

299
00:12:30,320 --> 00:12:30,510
[Billiards Is a Way of Life.]

300
00:12:30,510 --> 00:12:31,240
Sir.

301
00:12:31,360 --> 00:12:32,420
Get me some tokens.

302
00:12:32,430 --> 00:12:33,270
Coming.

303
00:12:37,120 --> 00:12:38,020
Tianfei.

304
00:12:38,300 --> 00:12:39,300
Want more tokens?

305
00:12:40,480 --> 00:12:41,810
You still owe me 80,000.

306
00:12:41,990 --> 00:12:42,840
So,

307
00:12:43,270 --> 00:12:44,870
are you going to keep playing?

308
00:12:44,870 --> 00:12:46,200
Stop talking and hurry up.

309
00:12:46,200 --> 00:12:47,390
Bring some tokens over.

310
00:12:47,390 --> 00:12:48,360
Bring plenty.

311
00:12:49,050 --> 00:12:49,580
[Billiards Is a Way of Life.]

312
00:12:49,580 --> 00:12:50,490
Win more, okay?

313
00:12:51,550 --> 00:12:52,270
Scar,

314
00:12:52,270 --> 00:12:53,360
y-you're out!

315
00:12:53,630 --> 00:12:55,120
Don't mention this to me.

316
00:12:57,160 --> 00:12:58,390
Xiang took the blame.

317
00:12:59,300 --> 00:13:00,700
He got locked up instead.

318
00:13:05,140 --> 00:13:06,260
Tianfei?

319
00:13:07,100 --> 00:13:08,510
Come with us.

320
00:13:11,690 --> 00:13:13,020
[Rome Hotel]

321
00:13:13,020 --> 00:13:13,770
Bo,

322
00:13:14,310 --> 00:13:14,920
he's here.

323
00:13:16,950 --> 00:13:18,210
You're here, Tianfei.

324
00:13:20,080 --> 00:13:21,080
What's going on?

325
00:13:21,670 --> 00:13:23,960
If you have business, talk to my brother.

326
00:13:23,960 --> 00:13:25,290
Why are you grabbing me?

327
00:13:26,610 --> 00:13:27,810
I don't owe you money.

328
00:13:30,510 --> 00:13:31,840
How much does he owe you?

329
00:13:32,010 --> 00:13:33,870
Mr. Luo, he's 80,000 short with me.

330
00:13:33,870 --> 00:13:34,720
Go get 80,000.

331
00:13:49,190 --> 00:13:49,830
Take it.

332
00:13:51,750 --> 00:13:52,750
I'll take it then.

333
00:13:53,270 --> 00:13:54,230
Thank you, Mr. Luo.

334
00:13:54,230 --> 00:13:54,830
You can go.

335
00:13:57,440 --> 00:13:58,040
Tianfei.

336
00:13:58,720 --> 00:14:00,910
Now you owe me money.

337
00:14:01,720 --> 00:14:02,930
My rule here is

338
00:14:02,960 --> 00:14:04,440
10,000 yuan per finger.

339
00:14:05,180 --> 00:14:07,910
Which two fingers do you want to keep?

340
00:14:21,270 --> 00:14:22,600
Quite a temper you have.

341
00:14:23,840 --> 00:14:27,600
You agree that paying debts
is only right, don't you?

342
00:14:30,620 --> 00:14:31,260
Yes.

343
00:14:32,520 --> 00:14:33,920
Nothing wrong with that.

344
00:14:34,160 --> 00:14:36,620
But it's not that I don't
want to pay you back.

345
00:14:36,750 --> 00:14:37,670
My money...

346
00:14:38,640 --> 00:14:40,770
My money is tied up in the stock market.

347
00:14:41,180 --> 00:14:43,580
How could you
get stuck in this bull market?

348
00:14:44,580 --> 00:14:46,180
Did you buy high and sell low?

349
00:14:46,840 --> 00:14:47,970
You know your stuff.

350
00:14:48,790 --> 00:14:49,990
You trade stocks too?

351
00:14:53,750 --> 00:14:54,640
Then

352
00:14:54,750 --> 00:14:56,390
give me some tips.

353
00:14:57,010 --> 00:14:58,540
Don't buy blindly anymore.

354
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:01,060
I'll give you tips on what to buy next.

355
00:15:01,260 --> 00:15:02,470
Okay.

356
00:15:03,270 --> 00:15:05,360
Let's get back to the 80,000 yuan.

357
00:15:05,690 --> 00:15:07,620
Actually, we can still negotiate.

358
00:15:07,880 --> 00:15:08,830
About the land,

359
00:15:09,230 --> 00:15:10,890
help me figure something out.

360
00:15:11,070 --> 00:15:11,880
The land...

361
00:15:12,670 --> 00:15:14,860
Coming to me about land issues is useless.

362
00:15:14,860 --> 00:15:16,620
I have no say in Longwan.

363
00:15:17,120 --> 00:15:20,070
Madam Wen and Tianye are in charge there.

364
00:15:20,560 --> 00:15:23,290
It's pointless to come to me.

365
00:15:23,640 --> 00:15:25,160
I-I'm nobody.

366
00:15:28,300 --> 00:15:30,300
Does he think I'm joking?

367
00:15:32,310 --> 00:15:33,740
Is it because I don't look

368
00:15:34,450 --> 00:15:35,850
tough enough?

369
00:15:39,120 --> 00:15:40,000
Stop joking.

370
00:15:41,340 --> 00:15:42,100
Go bring him.

371
00:15:44,170 --> 00:15:44,810
Hurry up.

372
00:15:49,440 --> 00:15:50,570
How much does he owe?

373
00:15:50,650 --> 00:15:51,260
10,000.

374
00:15:51,760 --> 00:15:52,820
Hold his hand here.

375
00:15:59,930 --> 00:16:00,960
Are you sure it's 10,000?

376
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:01,680
10,000.

377
00:16:10,490 --> 00:16:13,780
[Taxi]

378
00:16:18,640 --> 00:16:19,420
Tao.

379
00:16:20,760 --> 00:16:22,610
Who's that taxi driver?

380
00:16:23,990 --> 00:16:25,150
You mean Mai?

381
00:16:26,950 --> 00:16:28,100
He's like

382
00:16:28,410 --> 00:16:30,560
Captain Qin and your former Captain Hu,

383
00:16:30,560 --> 00:16:32,160
all Director Ye's protégés.

384
00:16:32,590 --> 00:16:33,510
Also a cop?

385
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:34,470
He was,

386
00:16:34,770 --> 00:16:35,680
but now...

387
00:16:37,270 --> 00:16:38,130
What happened?

388
00:16:39,030 --> 00:16:40,440
Did something go wrong?

389
00:16:41,550 --> 00:16:42,440
Have you heard?

390
00:16:42,480 --> 00:16:44,240
Crazy used to work
at the Municipal Bureau too,

391
00:16:44,240 --> 00:16:46,440
before being transferred
to the police station.

392
00:16:46,440 --> 00:16:47,570
I've heard about it.

393
00:16:47,990 --> 00:16:49,110
It's the same case.

394
00:16:50,080 --> 00:16:52,550
A sexual assault case
6 years ago. The Xu Li case.

395
00:16:52,550 --> 00:16:54,280
Crazy, Mai

396
00:16:54,320 --> 00:16:56,120
and Xiaoyue were in charge of it.

397
00:16:56,540 --> 00:16:58,140
That case ended tragically.

398
00:16:58,510 --> 00:17:00,000
Xu Li couldn't take it
and committed suicide.

399
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:00,450
Her family was also harassed
by a gang of thugs.

400
00:17:00,450 --> 00:17:01,840
[Hanzhou City; 2002]

401
00:17:01,840 --> 00:17:02,790
You beast!

402
00:17:03,120 --> 00:17:04,599
You ruined my daughter!

403
00:17:05,640 --> 00:17:06,700
What are you doing?

404
00:17:07,480 --> 00:17:08,520
What are you doing?

405
00:17:08,520 --> 00:17:09,400
Come on!

406
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:11,430
Kill me and I'll haunt you forever!

407
00:17:11,849 --> 00:17:12,720
Police!

408
00:17:12,829 --> 00:17:14,630
Let go!

409
00:17:14,720 --> 00:17:15,640
What're you doing?

410
00:17:15,640 --> 00:17:16,369
What're you doing?

411
00:17:16,369 --> 00:17:16,750
What're you doing?

412
00:17:16,750 --> 00:17:17,440
Go away!

413
00:17:19,020 --> 00:17:20,650
We're just here to offer condolences.

414
00:17:20,650 --> 00:17:21,130
Get out!

415
00:17:29,590 --> 00:17:30,600
Pick this up.

416
00:17:31,890 --> 00:17:32,790
What if I don't?

417
00:17:32,940 --> 00:17:34,180
Don't push your luck.

418
00:17:34,790 --> 00:17:36,570
I said pick it up!

419
00:17:36,960 --> 00:17:38,180
I won't do it.

420
00:17:43,060 --> 00:17:43,720
Don't move!

421
00:17:51,440 --> 00:17:52,150
Freeze!

422
00:18:01,110 --> 00:18:01,550
Stay still!

423
00:18:01,550 --> 00:18:02,660
Mai lost his temper

424
00:18:02,690 --> 00:18:04,560
and couldn't help beating those guys up.

425
00:18:04,560 --> 00:18:05,580
The situation escalated

426
00:18:05,580 --> 00:18:06,990
and he ended up in jail.

427
00:18:07,460 --> 00:18:09,860
Crazy was also affected by this incident,

428
00:18:09,880 --> 00:18:11,570
which is why
he was transferred to the police station.

429
00:18:11,570 --> 00:18:12,700
What happened next?

430
00:18:12,830 --> 00:18:14,310
Did they find the culprit?

431
00:18:15,270 --> 00:18:16,660
They made a sketch back then,

432
00:18:16,660 --> 00:18:18,680
but it was too vague to identify anyone.

433
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:20,340
So the case was left unsolved.

434
00:18:20,650 --> 00:18:23,140
That's why Mai fell out with Director Ye.

435
00:18:25,570 --> 00:18:26,470
No wonder.

436
00:18:27,290 --> 00:18:27,820
[Jiu's Restaurant]

437
00:18:27,820 --> 00:18:28,420
Jiu.

438
00:18:29,310 --> 00:18:31,550
Didn't I ask you before about

439
00:18:32,590 --> 00:18:35,250
that roaming
underground gambling operation?

440
00:18:35,330 --> 00:18:36,530
What did you find out?

441
00:18:37,850 --> 00:18:39,850
That's a tough one, Captain Qin.

442
00:18:40,770 --> 00:18:42,780
They operate like guerrillas.

443
00:18:43,030 --> 00:18:44,090
Hard to track down.

444
00:18:44,570 --> 00:18:46,750
They just set up a tent
in the wilderness and start operating.

445
00:18:46,750 --> 00:18:49,080
You can't get in without knowing someone.

446
00:18:49,240 --> 00:18:50,900
Why are you being so hesitant?

447
00:18:51,160 --> 00:18:53,310
Just go in and get the information.

448
00:18:53,310 --> 00:18:55,310
You don't need to
worry about anything else.

449
00:18:55,310 --> 00:18:58,350
Mai, it's not...

450
00:18:58,350 --> 00:18:59,400
Not that simple.

451
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:01,000
I can't get in there.

452
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:02,510
They have guards posted

453
00:19:02,510 --> 00:19:03,960
2 or 3 kilometers out.

454
00:19:03,960 --> 00:19:05,350
And they've got all kinds of

455
00:19:05,350 --> 00:19:07,070
infrared sensors, ultraviolet detectors,

456
00:19:07,070 --> 00:19:08,310
heat sensors... I don't
even understand it all.

457
00:19:08,310 --> 00:19:10,630
But if you go in,
they'll spot you immediately.

458
00:19:10,630 --> 00:19:11,550
Not just people,

459
00:19:11,550 --> 00:19:12,830
even dogs can't get in.

460
00:19:13,400 --> 00:19:14,130
You just need

461
00:19:14,310 --> 00:19:15,510
to be responsible for

462
00:19:15,750 --> 00:19:16,970
finding out how many people are there

463
00:19:16,970 --> 00:19:18,540
and telling us the exact location.

464
00:19:18,540 --> 00:19:19,760
Mai will handle the rest.

465
00:19:19,760 --> 00:19:21,400
I do the hard work,

466
00:19:21,710 --> 00:19:23,470
you do the easy stuff.

467
00:19:23,490 --> 00:19:24,680
What's so difficult about it?

468
00:19:24,680 --> 00:19:25,550
It's not difficult.

469
00:19:25,550 --> 00:19:26,790
So that's settled then.

470
00:19:26,790 --> 00:19:27,750
Let's eat.

471
00:19:27,750 --> 00:19:29,440
If you need more, I'll add dishes.

472
00:19:29,440 --> 00:19:33,220
[Martyrs' Cemetery of Hanzhou]

473
00:19:41,480 --> 00:19:42,310
Sichen.

474
00:19:43,330 --> 00:19:44,930
Your dad and I came to see you.

475
00:19:47,300 --> 00:19:48,630
You're Qin Feng, right?

476
00:19:49,090 --> 00:19:49,480
Yes.

477
00:19:49,510 --> 00:19:50,120
Hello.

478
00:19:50,140 --> 00:19:50,780
Ye Siyuan.

479
00:19:50,850 --> 00:19:51,440
Hello.

480
00:19:51,470 --> 00:19:52,310
[Ye Siyuan, Ye Tianyou's nephew]

481
00:19:52,310 --> 00:19:53,910
My uncle mentions you often.

482
00:19:54,540 --> 00:19:56,210
Director Ye has
mentioned you to me as well.

483
00:19:56,210 --> 00:19:56,860
Really?

484
00:19:58,330 --> 00:19:59,660
What did he say about me?

485
00:20:00,880 --> 00:20:02,810
He said you're quite outstanding.

486
00:20:05,730 --> 00:20:06,430
Honey.

487
00:20:07,170 --> 00:20:08,920
Can you take a day off tomorrow?

488
00:20:08,950 --> 00:20:11,600
Mom needs a follow-up check-up.
Could you go with her?

489
00:20:11,600 --> 00:20:14,090
I just started at the Municipal Bureau.
I can't take time off.

490
00:20:14,090 --> 00:20:15,350
Okay, thank you.

491
00:20:15,570 --> 00:20:16,840
Okay. I'll hang up now.

492
00:20:16,870 --> 00:20:17,590
Wang Tao.

493
00:20:18,630 --> 00:20:19,490
Captain Zhong.

494
00:20:26,930 --> 00:20:27,930
Where's Qin Feng?

495
00:20:28,180 --> 00:20:29,340
He went out.

496
00:20:29,970 --> 00:20:31,430
Why didn't you go with him?

497
00:20:31,800 --> 00:20:33,200
Director Ye is visiting his son's grave.

498
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:35,080
He went with Director Peng
to accompany him.

499
00:20:35,080 --> 00:20:35,960
They didn't ask me to go,

500
00:20:35,960 --> 00:20:38,490
and it wouldn't be
appropriate for me to join.

501
00:20:39,950 --> 00:20:41,210
What about the report?

502
00:20:41,490 --> 00:20:43,370
I'll get it for you right away.

503
00:20:48,150 --> 00:20:49,810
Why wasn't I invited?

504
00:20:53,680 --> 00:20:54,550
You just said

505
00:20:55,270 --> 00:20:57,470
that Mai often comes to see Sichen?

506
00:20:58,050 --> 00:20:58,770
Yes.

507
00:20:58,790 --> 00:21:00,990
Whenever he has time, he comes to visit.

508
00:21:02,880 --> 00:21:03,880
Thank him for me.

509
00:21:04,240 --> 00:21:04,920
I will.

510
00:21:06,610 --> 00:21:08,820
Now that you've taken
Hu Xiaoyue's position,

511
00:21:08,820 --> 00:21:10,550
how do you plan to investigate?

512
00:21:12,710 --> 00:21:13,660
I'll start with

513
00:21:14,320 --> 00:21:15,270
Wang Ming.

514
00:21:15,540 --> 00:21:17,470
I'll pick up where Xiaoyue left off

515
00:21:17,830 --> 00:21:20,290
and continue the investigation from there.

516
00:21:20,330 --> 00:21:21,530
It won't be that easy.

517
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:24,330
Who do you think might be involved?

518
00:21:26,550 --> 00:21:27,480
Well,

519
00:21:27,960 --> 00:21:29,300
I don't want to speculate.

520
00:21:29,300 --> 00:21:31,160
We'll know after investigating.

521
00:21:31,310 --> 00:21:33,270
Do you have any concerns, Director Ye?

522
00:21:33,270 --> 00:21:34,870
You don't need to provoke me.

523
00:21:35,720 --> 00:21:37,850
How you investigate is your business.

524
00:21:37,930 --> 00:21:40,170
But there's one thing you must remember.

525
00:21:40,170 --> 00:21:41,100
Follow protocol

526
00:21:41,560 --> 00:21:43,090
and keep me updated as things develop.

527
00:21:43,090 --> 00:21:43,890
I understand.

528
00:21:43,910 --> 00:21:45,370
Don't worry, Director Ye.

529
00:21:58,440 --> 00:21:59,350
No more bets.

530
00:22:02,510 --> 00:22:03,500
-Bo.
-Bo.

531
00:22:04,680 --> 00:22:05,650
No more bets.

532
00:22:07,750 --> 00:22:08,440
Mr. Zhou,

533
00:22:08,440 --> 00:22:09,440
how's your luck?

534
00:22:10,350 --> 00:22:11,750
